@startuml activity-directory-open
'' PlantUML over Mermaid: swimlanes show WHICH layer owns each step of opening a directory; the
'' directory? branch and the "same vv:content spine — no new IPC" note are activity-diagram features a
'' flowchart cannot lane. Colours are the shared per-concept palette (_vv-theme.iuml).
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Open a directory → in-pane browser (piggybacks the vv:open / vv:content spine)

|#E3F2ED|Renderer|
start
:folder click / URI bar / Alt+Down →\n[:doc/open dir] or [:tab/navigate dir];
:nav/nav-active pushes a history entry;
:fx [:vv/open dir];

|#F4F1E1|IPC seam|
:window.vv.open(dir) → vv:open;

|#E4E8F1|Main (Node)|
:vinary.main.service/open!;
if (directory? path) then (yes)
  :list-dir → [{:name :path :dir? :size :mtime :symlink} …];
  :send **vv:content** {:kind "directory" :entries …};
  :watch path {ignoreInitial true, **depth 0**}\nadd / unlink / addDir / unlinkDir → re-list (live-refresh);
  note right: bounded depth-0 watch\n(an ADR-0006 amendment)
else (file)
  :read + send file content (unchanged);
endif

|#F4F1E1|IPC seam|
:onContent → [:content/received];

|#E3F2ED|Renderer (re-frame)|
:event (PURE): attrs gain :doc/entries (vec entries);
:record-recent → [:ui :recent]\ntrail (dir→child) + (file only) recent-files MRU;
:fx [:vv/save-recent] (debounced 300ms → recent.edn);

|#EEE6EF|Stores|
:**:ds/transact** {:doc/path :doc/kind "directory" :doc/entries};
:bridge → [:ds/changed] → :ds/rev inc (:doc/active recomputes);

|#E3E7F2|DOM / app-db|
:content-view branch (= "directory" (:doc/kind doc));
:**dir-view** (pure Reagent): detailed list,\nsort dirs-first; highlight = nav/effective-selected;
stop

legend right
  |= Colour |= Swimlane |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer (re-frame events + fx) |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| IPC seam (preload / window.vv) |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Main process (Node IO) |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Stores (DataScript) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DOM / app-db (dir-view) |
endlegend
@enduml
